									<p>Whether you define just one job, which is how most people start with Workforce Optimization at a company, or tackle all of the jobs for just one department, or all of the jobs for all of the department, the Job Tasks form let's you define the tasks done as part of a specific job, the performance factors that each task affects, and what skills, knowledge, and behaviors someone must have to successfully do each job task. It also captures the Accountability and Success factors for the job, the career path next step, required training classes, and questions one should ask when interviewing a candidate for the job. One screen lets you document your Organization Design efforts - and use them later for Talent Development</p>
