								<div class="col-md-12 col-sm-12 margin-bottom-20">
									<p class="size-20 text-center">Which creates an Automatic Historical Profile of Every Employee in the Employee Profile Feature</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-12 col-sm-6 margin-bottom-20">
									<p>You build an employee's historical profile one change at a time over a long career, so the entire historical profile of an employee is available. Once you know your company's top performers, you can start to look at their backgrounds to identify common elements. If keeping the data is the first step to understanding, then easy access and use of it must be step two.</p>
									<p class="size-20 text-center">Record Employee Reviews and Task Coaching with the Employee Review Features</p>
									<p>Whether it's a review to coach for job performance, or the official Accountability Review, often review notes are either not kept at all, or are stored in a disconnected system. With <span style="font-family:Orbitron">P.E.R.F.O.R.M.</span>, when someone has taken the time to observe an employee's job performance, review notes can be stored and retrieved along with all the other pertinent employee data. There's several screens that let you catalog an employee's development plan, and also an area that let's you record formal accountability reviews.</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6">
									<img class="pull-right img-responsive" src="/static/images/perform8.jpg" alt="" />
									<p class="text-left">The Employee Profile screen is an automatic assembly of all current and past active information.</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6">
									<p class="size-20">Training Results and Employee Reviews enable The Best Practices Feature</p>
									<p>Part of <span style="font-family:Orbitron">P.E.R.F.O.R.M.</span>'s Employee Review feature is the ability to flag when an employee is doing a job task really well. These review notes establish Best Practices for those job tasks. When someone else wants to improve his/her scores for a performance measurement, he/she can review the Best Practices for tasks affecting the measurement, and learn from the success of others!</p>
									<p>Over time, it's important to see what an employee has done to correct disparities in job task performance. Documenting corrective actions helps to focus the employee's development, and also begins to identify what brings the best results when trying to develop any employee's ability to perform a job task. Most companies have only an educated best guess at what works. <span style="font-family:Orbitron">P.E.R.F.O.R.M.</span> helps you make decisions based on facts! As you watch the corresponding Employee Performance Measurements go up or down, you learn what learning experiences bring the best (and worst) results.</p>
