									<img class="pull-right img-responsive" src="/static/images/Perform10.jpg" alt="" />
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-12 col-sm-6">
									<p>The Learning Activities feature is an online Course Catalog, while the Registration features let you register someone or see who's coming to one of your events.</p>
									<p><span style="font-family:Orbitron">P.E.R.F.O.R.M.</span> catalogs (and is searchable!) the formal courses or other learning experiences at your company. Many facets of a learning experience, including scheduled sessions, learning outcomes, and S,K,& B's developed, are detailed here. Job tasks (from the Jobs area) become terminal learning objectives here, and the S,K,& B's the job tasks require can be modularized and reused as enabling learning objectives.</p>
									<p>Often you need to know who is registered for a session. The Registration By Activity form lets you manage registration based on the event. You can register new participants, and alter or even delete those already signed up. The print features available for events include a Class List, an Activity Description (a.k.a. Course Description), and more. This form also lets you credit employees with completing the activity too!</p>
									<p class="size-20 text-center">Course Options and Employee History enable The Career Planning Feature</p>
									<p>The Career Planning worksheet lets an employee review what he/she has accomplished and identify what must be mastered to move into a selected future job role. Because <span style="font-family:Orbitron">P.E.R.F.O.R.M.</span> has both the job role details AND the employee's historical profile, it is easy to gain insight as to how to get from where they are to where they want to be.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

